[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dee Gordon: Miami Marlins player banned for 80 games after positive drugs test

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Reigning National League batting champion Dee Gordon has been suspended for 80 games after testing positive for performance-enhancing drugs.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Major League Baseball said the Miami Marlins player, 28, tested positive for exogenous testosterone and clostebol.
The second baseman, who led the major leagues in hits and stolen bases last season, is the seventh player suspended this year under the MLB drug plan.
Marlins president David Samson said the club "don't condone" Gordon's actions.
